{"parentUuid":"f2ff944f-6672-4061-8113-6e5a0eece7ef","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"e13b644f-9343-499a-8d34-78ca26a90b58","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"ade9ea237ba60cf3e","slug":"wild-tumbling-fountain","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EEvB8gwkKWyu1GfwBdPxjt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright 2026 The Formal Conjectures Authors.\n     3→\n     4→Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→\n     8→    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→\n    10→Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→limitations under the License.\n    15→-/\n    16→\n    17→import FormalConjectures.Util.ProblemImports\n    18→\n    19→/-!\n    20→# Erdős Problem 190\n    21→\n    22→*Reference:* [erdosproblems.com/190](https://www.erdosproblems.com/190)\n    23→\n    24→Let $H(k)$ be the smallest $N$ such that in any finite colouring of $\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$\n    25→(into any number of colours) there is always either a monochromatic $k$-term\n    26→arithmetic progression or a rainbow arithmetic progression (i.e. all\n    27→elements are different colours). Estimate $H(k)$. Is it true that\n    28→$H(k)^{1/k}/k \\to \\infty$ as $k \\to \\infty$?\n    29→\n    30→This type of problem belongs to 'canonical' Ramsey theory. The existence\n    31→of $H(k)$ follows from Szemerédi's theorem, and it is easy to show that\n    32→$H(k)^{1/k} \\to \\infty$.\n    33→\n    34→[ErGr80] Erdős, P. and Graham, R., _Old and new problems and results in combinatorial\n    35→number theory_. Monographies de L'Enseignement Mathématique (1980).\n    36→-/\n    37→\n    38→open Filter Real\n    39→\n    40→namespace Erdos190\n    41→\n    42→/-- A colouring $\\chi : \\mathbb{N} \\to \\mathbb{N}$ has a monochromatic $k$-term arithmetic\n    43→progression within $\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$: there exist $a \\geq 1$ and $d \\geq 1$ such that\n    44→$a, a+d, \\ldots, a+(k-1) \\cdot d$ are all in $\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ and all share the same colour. -/\n    45→def HasMonoAP (χ : ℕ → ℕ) (N k : ℕ) : Prop :=\n    46→  ∃ a d : ℕ, 0 < d ∧ 1 ≤ a ∧ a + (k - 1) * d ≤ N ∧\n    47→    ∀ i : ℕ, i < k → χ (a + i * d) = χ a\n    48→\n    49→/-- A colouring $\\chi : \\mathbb{N} \\to \\mathbb{N}$ has a rainbow $3$-term arithmetic\n    50→progression within $\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$: there exist $a \\geq 1$ and $d \\geq 1$ such that\n    51→$a, a+d, a+2d$ are all in $\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ and their colours are pairwise distinct. -/\n    52→def HasRainbowAP (χ : ℕ → ℕ) (N : ℕ) : Prop :=\n    53→  ∃ a d : ℕ, 0 < d ∧ 1 ≤ a ∧ a + 2 * d ≤ N ∧\n    54→    χ a ≠ χ (a + d) ∧ χ a ≠ χ (a + 2 * d) ∧ χ (a + d) ≠ χ (a + 2 * d)\n    55→\n    56→/-- $H(k)$ is the smallest $N$ such that any colouring of $\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ contains\n    57→either a monochromatic $k$-term AP or a rainbow $3$-term AP. -/\n    58→noncomputable def H (k : ℕ) : ℕ :=\n    59→  sInf {N : ℕ | ∀ χ : ℕ → ℕ, HasMonoAP χ N k ∨ HasRainbowAP χ N}\n    60→\n    61→/--\n    62→Erdős Problem 190 [ErGr80]:\n    63→\n    64→Is it true that $H(k)^{1/k}/k \\to \\infty$ as $k \\to \\infty$, where $H(k)$ is the smallest $N$\n    65→such that any finite colouring of $\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ always contains either a monochromatic\n    66→$k$-term arithmetic progression or a rainbow arithmetic progression?\n    67→-/\n    68→@[category research open, AMS 5]\n    69→theorem erdos_190 : answer(sorry) ↔\n    70→    Tendsto (fun k : ℕ => (H k : ℝ) ^ ((1 : ℝ) / (k : ℝ)) / (k : ℝ)) atTop atTop := by\n    71→  sorry\n    72→\n    73→end Erdos190\n    74→"}]},"uuid":"6ebbdbdf-f7a2-45f8-9923-3e3419482065","timestamp":"2026-03-10T02:44:09.490Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f2ff944f-6672-4061-8113-6e5a0eece7ef"}
